node.text: ad| nearly 3 years on the @wagamama_uk menu, my collab dish avant-gard’n is coming off the menu 🥺 but it’s not all sad, my vegan egg will still be featured on the menu, this time in a new vegan dish wagamama have created called the ‘no duck donburi’ - check the video to see what I think of it. The dish is available exclusively on Deliveroo for the rest of the month before it goes into the UK’s wagamama restaurants from 6 october. check out wagamama’s plant pledge - link in bio. they’re asking everyone to join their journey and make a pledge for the planet by eating more plants 🌱 thank you to everyone that showed up to the events, ordered the avant-gard’n, to all the wagamama chefs, servers & staff, to @mox_london & everyone else that helped make this happen, It’s still one of my biggest and proudest achievements to have a dish on the menu. Goodbye avant-gard’n ♥️ PS ITS STILL AVAILABLE AT @wagamamaus restaurants !! 🇺🇸 Big love Gaz

node.text:
Thicc, creamy & spiced with chilli. Recipe below! Have a great weekend ✨

3 cups/750ml @besproud Unsweetened Pea Milk

1 Vanilla Pod, split down the middle & seeds extracted

1 cup/100g Dark Chocolate, chopped small

3 tbs Cacao Powder 

1/2 tsp Ground Cinnamon 

Pinch Dried Chilli Flakes 

3 tbs Maple Syrup or Sugar of your choice

3 tbs Cornflour 

1/2 cup/125ml @besproud unsweetened Pea Milk

Pinch Sea Salt 

Method -

Gently heat the milk in a medium-sized saucepan, with the vanilla pod & seeds.

When the milk is simmering remove the pod, then whisk in the cacao, cinnamon, chilli, maple & chopped chocolate. 

Add the cornflour to a mixing bowl and add the 1/4 cup of milk and whisk together until smooth. 

Whisk the cornflour mixture into the hot chocolate. You will gradually see it thicken up. If it thickens too much just let it down with a little extra milk. 

Add the salt, then serve. 

I topped mine with some sproud barista milk froth, grated chocolate & chilli flakes.

node.text: ad| nearly 3 years on the @wagamama_uk menu, my collab dish avant-gard’n is coming off the menu 🥺 but it’s not all sad, my vegan egg will still be featured on the menu, this time in a new vegan dish wagamama have created called the ‘no duck donburi’ - check the video to see what I think of it. The dish is available exclusively on Deliveroo for the rest of the month before it goes into the UK’s wagamama restaurants from 6 october. check out wagamama’s plant pledge - link in bio. they’re asking everyone to join their journey and make a pledge for the planet by eating more plants 🌱 thank you to everyone that showed up to the events, ordered the avant-gard’n, to all the wagamama chefs, servers & staff, to @mox_london & everyone else that helped make this happen, It’s still one of my biggest and proudest achievements to have a dish on the menu. Goodbye avant-gard’n ♥️ PS ITS STILL AVAILABLE AT @wagamamaus restaurants !! 🇺🇸 Big love Gaz

node.text: ad | Spicy Quinoa Enchiladas 🌶🔥 link in my IG bio for the recipe! packed with nutritious Mexican-Style @merchantgourmet grains - with a spicy flavour, peppers, mushrooms & complete with homemade enchilada sauce, all simple to make but super tasty. node.text: 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁷󠁬󠁳󠁿 This is ‘Bara Brith’ & it’s probably my favourite cake. Bara brith is a traditional Welsh tea bread flavoured with tea, dried fruits and spices. It’s not as popular as it once was in Wales, but hopeful my veganised recipe will change that, it’s super simple to make & my recipe can be found if you click the link in my Instagram bio. Give it a try please 🙏❤️ Gaz #VEGAN
